.TH RTSP-BRUTE-FORCE 1 "June 2026" "rtsp-brute-force-tool 3.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rtsp-brute-force \- assess RTSP credential security
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rtsp-brute-force
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
RTSP Brute Force Tool performs authorized RTSP credential-security assessments
with camera-vendor presets, configurable stream paths, rate limiting, parallel
workers, and machine-readable reports.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-url " " URL
Set the target RTSP URL.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-vendor " " NAME
Use a camera-vendor preset.
.TP
.B \-\-vendor-defaults
Use the selected vendor's default credentials.
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Show the planned task count without connecting to the target.
.TP
.B \-\-list-vendors
List available vendor presets.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show complete command-line help.
.SH EXAMPLE
.B rtsp-brute-force -u rtsp://192.0.2.10:554/ -V hikvision --vendor-defaults --dry-run
